# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Mirpur-10 Traffic AI Research Repository
# Q1-Level: Only reproducible, peer-reviewable code & schemas go to GitHub.
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
# 🔴 SECRETS — NEVER commit these (would expose Supabase, Mapbox, Tomorrow.io)
# =============================================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*
secrets.json
gcp-sa-key.json
*.json.key
service-account*.json


# =============================================================================
# 🔴 ML MODEL BINARY ARTIFACTS
# model_ml_weight.json is a ~750KB XGBoost binary blob.
# It is stored in Supabase Storage and fetched at runtime by the collector.
# Committing large binaries bloats git history permanently.
# Reproducibility: re-train via `python trainer_xgb.py` with the same seed.
# =============================================================================
backend/model_ml_weight.json
*.json.model
*.ubj
*.pkl
*.joblib


# =============================================================================
# 🔴 RAW DATA DUMPS — Data lives in Supabase, not in the repo
# logs.json / logs2.json are local snapshots for debugging only.
# A Q1 repo points to the Supabase data source, not raw dumps.
# =============================================================================
logs.json
logs2.json
*.data.json
data_dump*.json
data_dump*.csv
*.csv
*.xlsx
*.parquet

# 🟢 ALLOW GENERATED REPORTS & XAI WEIGHTS (CI/CD OUTPUTS)
!backend/reports/
!backend/reports/*.csv
!backend/*_weights.csv
!backend/*_feature_importance.csv

# 🔴 IGNORE DEEP LEARNING MODEL WEIGHTS
*.pth
*.pt


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 PYTHON RUNTIME ARTIFACTS
# =============================================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.pyo
.Python
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENTS — Use requirements.txt to reproduce the env
# =============================================================================
venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/
.conda/
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
site/


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 IDE & EDITOR FILES — Not part of the research artifact
# =============================================================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace
*.swp
*.swo
*~


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 OS-GENERATED JUNK
# =============================================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 TOOL-SPECIFIC DIRECTORIES (local AI/IDE tooling)
# =============================================================================
.qodo/
.sixth/
.gemini/


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 FRONTEND BUILD ARTIFACTS (if frontend exists)
# =============================================================================
node_modules/
.next/
.nuxt/
dist/
build/
.eslintcache
*.tsbuildinfo


# =============================================================================
# 🟡 LOGS
# =============================================================================
*.log
backend/traffic_pipeline.log
logs/


# =============================================================================
# 🟢 LOCAL WORKING DOCUMENTS — Research notes, not peer-reviewed artifacts
# These are session-specific working files. The final paper replaces them.
# Keep in local workspace; push only the final cleaned README & SQL schemas.
# =============================================================================
mirpur_traffic_A2Z_fix_list.md
Q1_hostile_reviewer_additional_findings.md
mirpur_verified_references.md
mirpur_traffic_complete_references.md
implementation_plan.md
frontend_q1_review.md
